public class Error

  • Method Details

    • duplicate

      public static <T extends Error> T duplicate​(T event)
      Duplicate the event.

      Returns a new event with the same class and the same properties of the given event. Relies on the proper implementation of constructors “<T extendError> T(T event)” for derived classes.

      Creating a duplicate id useful for forwarding a derived Error while handling a base class.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the generic type
      Parameters:
      event - the event
      Returns:
      the t
